) Taiwan legislator Hsu Chih-chieh held a joint Taiwanese and Japanese international press conference about global legislation to combat forced organ harvesting on July 15, 2024. The human rights legislative committee of the Legislative Yuan invited a former doctor from China, Zheng Zhi, to speak at the press conference. Zheng Zhi was an intern in the Department of Urology at the Shenyang Army General Hospital when he participated in the Chinese Communist PartyтАЩs (CCP) live organ harvesting. He said hopes to tell more people about the atrocities that he witnessed.

In addition to Taiwanese legislators Hsu Chih-chieh and Chen Zhao-zi, representatives of the Taiwan Medical Association and the Taiwan Lawyers Association expressed their support for legislation on organ harvesting. Hiroaki Maruyama, the chairman of JapanтАЩs тАЬStop Medical Genocide тАУ Society for the Study of Organ Transplantation in ChinaтАЭ (SMG Network) also attended the event.


International press conference in Taiwan on тАЬLegislation to combat organ harvestingтАЭ on July 15, 2024

Zheng Zhi was an intern at the Department of Urology at the Shenyang Army General Hospital, when in 1994, he, three other military doctors, a head nurse and a female nurse were asked to participate in a secret military mission. He was ordered to harvest the organs of an army officer who was under the age of 18.

Zheng Zhi said that at that time, the young officerтАЩs hands, feet and neck were tied with thin ropes, and there were soldiers with submachine guns standing guard nearby. After the head nurse cut open the clothes for disinfection, a military doctor directly disemboweled the patient without using anesthesia. He made a large incision from under the xiphoid process (under the sternum) and cut directly to the umbilicus. The intestines were removed.

At that time, the medical providers were divided into two groups, each removing the left and right kidneys. A military doctor ordered Zheng Zhi to cut open the artery and vein, and when he did, blood gushed out. He recalled, тАЬI immediately knew he was still alive, because the blood in the abdominal cavity was flowing.тАЭ

Then, the military doctor ordered him to remove the eyeball, but after taking off the bandage wrapped around his face, he said, тАЬI saw the young officerтАЩs eyes looking straight at me, and his eyelids were still moving. I said I really couldnтАЩt do it. I really couldnтАЩt do it. The other military doctor immediately took the hemostatic forceps and pressed the [young officerтАЩs] forehead, and then directly dug out the eyeball with his right hand,тАЭ Zheng Zhi related, as he wept.

тАЬAfter going through all this, I was about to collapse. I really couldnтАЩt take any more. I quickly asked the director for a leave to go home. This was a great shock to me. The young officer was less than 18 years old, almost the same age as me... such a vibrant life. But I didnтАЩt dare tell anyone. An officer warned me that if I told anyone, my life would be in danger.тАЭ

In 2005, a close confidant of a member of the CCPтАЩs Politburo Standing Committee who had a good relationship with Zheng ZhiтАЩs family visited him during the Chinese New Year and said, тАЬIn the basement of the rear garden of the Public Security Bureau in Wuhan, Hubei Province, there are many Falun Gong practitioners, including underage children.тАЭ
